
one-folder - synchronise your folders

Usage:
  onefolder --help
  onefolder --connect=<ip> --folder=<sync_folder>
      [--port=<listen-port>]

Options:
  -h --help  Prints a short usage summary.
  -c --connect=<ip>  Connect to the peer and start sharing.
  -f --folder=<sync_folder>  Perform the synchronisation on this folder
  -p --port=<listen_port>  Port used for listening for incoming connections

